#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use Debian::Debhelper::Dh_Lib;
use File::Path qw(remove_tree);

init();

# Clean up the old components directory
remove_tree('COMPONENTS', verbose=>1, safe=>1); 

exit(0);

=head1 NAME

dh_components_purge - purge components working directory

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<dh_components_purge> [S<I<debhelper options>>]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

C<dh_components_purge> is a debhelper program that removes the components
working directory.

=head1 CONFIGURATION

To enable this module it is necessary to pass the argument
C<--with components> to the C<dh> programa in the C<debian/rules>
file. See L<dh_components> for more details.

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<debhelper(1)>

This program is used with debhelper. 

L<quilt(1)>

=head1 AUTHOR

Nicholas Bamber <nicholas@periapt.co.uk>

=cut
